main event: Two unidentified objects were observed moving at high speeds in Covina, California on July 25, 1965.
interesting points: The objects were estimated to be traveling at speeds of 2000 mph and at thousands of miles high., The sighting lasted for approximately 20 minutes., The observer described the objects as disappearing by fading out of sight., One object moved southwest while the other moved northwest., No physical evidence of the objects was left behind.
